   <pb facs="117"/>
   <p>¶ Thou shalt vnderstāde, good Christen Reader, that imme<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>diately after this, as sone as may be, thou shalte haue the se<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>conde Booke, whiche entreate vpon as many thynges as this Booke doeth, bothe fruitfull to be knowen, and also most neces<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>sarye for these perillouse ty<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>mes: in the which, the Diuell doeth all, that he can, to extin<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>guish the trew Doctrine of the Gospell: whiche at this tyme, thorough our godly Magistra<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>tes, doeth reuiue, and florish a<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>gayne: Fare well, and pray, that we may performe the Woorke that we haue in haude.</p>
